y this cron session is active (no other sessions), send HEARTBEAT_OK only.\\nIf there are no sessions at all, stay SILENT.\\nCurrent time: Wednesday, April 15th, 2026 - 2:28 AM (UTC) / 2026-04-15 02:28 UTC\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"timestamp\": 1776220114011,\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"a1149296\",\n            \"seq\": 1\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Let me check the sessions_list to see what active sessions are running.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_6p3jngd8iccc_1\",\n              \"name\": \"sessions_list\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"limit\": 20,\n                \"activeMinutes\": 60,\n                \"messageLimit\": 3\n              }\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 345,\n            \"output\": 63,\n            \"totalTokens\": 14257,\n            \"cacheRead\": 10789,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 3060,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776220114188,\n          \"responseId\": \"062e2ad38f8c81654508734134ed716b\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"0c2fc162\",\n            \"seq\": 2\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"origin\": {\n        \"provider\": \"heartbeat\"\n      },\n      \"label\": \"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX\",\n      \"displayName\": \"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776220038460,\n      \"sessionId\": \"60f0623a-a186-4926-a3ac-b82f54b29e12\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 38491,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"running\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776199558073,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/60f0623a-a186-4926-a3ac-b82f54b29e12.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"The memory_get returned `disabled: true` with `error: \\\"path required\\\"` - meaning memory retrieval is unavailable. Let me check the heartbeat state file directly from the workspace filesystem.\\n\\nLet me also analyze the sessions list:\\n\\nCurrent active sessions (02:27 UTC):\\n1. `cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` — running (this is the cron itself!)\\n2. `cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` — running (QLHV 5p monitor)\\n3. `cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e` — running (Agent Status to Lead)\\n\\n\\n4. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134` — running (marked as \\\"running\\\" but actually ended earlier)\\n5. `agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:c2d275a5-d70a-4775-a268-fecf4708f133` — done\\n6. `agent:planner:subagent:63bb70ce-b5f3-48d0-a236-b6cf5d8d7922` — done\\n7. `agent:planner:subagent:ba49ac6d-ceff-4a9d-b3b1-7b89afdd88cc` — done\\n\\nI'm noticing several sessions marked as running but actually ended or completed, along with more finished subagents and orphaned cron jobs that appear stale.\\n\\nLooking at the last heartbeat state from 02:25 UTC, the DTLX 5p Monitor had been running for about 5 hours 41 minutes, which puts its start time around 20:44 UTC on April 14th. Now at 02:27 UTC on April 15th, it's been running for approximately 5 hours 43 minutes total.\\n\\nI'm also tracking several other cron jobs: the QLHV 5p monitor running for about 24 minutes, an agent status reporter just starting at 02:04 UTC, and a stale Telegram send cron that's been stuck for about 13 hours since April 14th at 13:04 UTC. There are also some completed tasks and an orphaned session to account for.\\n\\nAt 02:27 UTC, I'm seeing the DTLX monitor still running after nearly 5 hours 43 minutes, the QLHV monitor at about 24 minutes, and the agent status reporter at 23 minutes—so the system state looks stable with no significant changes from the previous check.\\n\\nI'm noticing a discrepancy though: the `telegram:group:-5163901258` session shows an ended timestamp that predates the 02:11 UTC message it contains, which suggests the delivery-mirror may be holding onto older messages in its session state rather than reflecting current reality.\\n\\nLooking back at the previous heartbeat state from 02:25 UTC, the cron job for the QLHV 5p monitor is marked as running with a start time of 02:03 UTC, and the system was stable at that point. Since then, the cron session itself appears to have ended at 02:03 UTC, so I need to verify whether the underlying monitor is still active or if it's truly terminated. I'm noticing a discrepancy between the sessions list showing cron:ed2d0b5d as running and the actual session data showing it ended much earlier at 02:03 UTC, suggesting the sessions list might be displaying cached or incorrectly reported status information.\\n\\nLooking at the heartbeat data, both cron jobs appear to have completed their cycles and restarted, but the updatedAt timestamps suggest they're still active—though I can't tell if these are actually new instances or just stale data from the previous runs.\\n\\nThe memory state check confirms the system was stable at 02:25 UTC with no new failures, new sessions, or blockers introduced, so the orphaned cron:ac986a8d remains unchanged. Since there's been no meaningful change to the system state, I should remain silent rather than trigger unnecessary notifications.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"No changes detected. System stable across all monitored sessions. Silent.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 24115,\n            \"output\": 865,\n            \"totalTokens\": 39356,\n            \"cacheRead\": 13944,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 432,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776220061369,\n          \"responseId\": \"062e2a9ec7e11f9f8c085634cb2d93d1\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"970f0f57\",\n            \"seq\": 5\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"origin\": {\n        \"provider\": \"heartbeat\"\n      },\n      \"label\": \"Cron: 5p Progress Report\",\n      \"displayName\": \"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776219903435,\n      \"sessionId\": \"c4073451-1822-40ea-9fce-12c378398d9b\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 45300,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"running\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776214290785,\n      \"endedAt\": 1776214477348,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 10277,\n      \"childSessions\": [\n        \"agent:master-orchestrator:subag